<br>
/agree with those who think that using Lag is something of a cheat<br>
<br>
As much as I would love to do whatever it takes to defend the home of my brothers and sisters (I have a fierce affiliation for any of the halfheight races), I was extraordinarily impressed by this example of roleplaying on Apep's part.  I believe that the gnomes should reply in kind: roleplaying with roleplaying.<br>
<br>
RPing varies on a day-to-day basis sometimes, and I know that I'm still searching for who Amaeliya really is and how she reacts to different situations.  It's easier for me because Amae and I are very similar in many of our aspects.<br>
<br>
In Apep's case it's different (I assume).  I would think that Apep's player wouldn't raid Chicago or whatever if his RL significant other had nasty family members there.  Thus he really has to get into his character's head and play him the way that Apep would react.<br>
<br>
/applaud Apep's player<br>
<br>
I cannot say gods all bless to either parties and must remain objective, but what I will do is thank Apep for bringing true roleplaying on a large scale into Norrath, and hope that my friends will not be killed.<br>
<br>
/em bows in respect to Apep and then melts back into the shadows<br>
<br>
